                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.48/255</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WJE1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-27T12:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 27, 1917, noon.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 6 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>379. Department’s 261, 16th. Foreign Office state Spanish Ambassador Berlin will
                    receive funds from American Commission for Jewish War Sufferers in Poland.
                    Ambassador suggests funds be transmitted as at present to Warburg &amp; Co.,
                    Hamburg, who will remit to central committee, Berlin, against receipts. Spanish
                    Ambassador adds that it will be impossible for either him or central committee
                    to purchase foodstuffs in Germany.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Willard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
